; BuildPlacementHandler + AttackMoveHandler are placed AFTER ClickHandler /
; BoxSelectHandler / DoubleClickSelect in sibling order so their
; _unhandled_input runs FIRST.
; Godot dispatches _unhandled_input in REVERSE sibling order — the
; higher-index sibling fires first. Verified by the regression test
; `test_godot_unhandled_input_dispatch_order` in
; tests/unit/test_godot_unhandled_input_dispatch_order.gd.
;
; BUG-10 fix (2026-05-14): the wave-1C placement put BPH at idx 4
; (between AttackMoveHandler and ClickHandler) under the mistaken
; "lower-index = first" convention. ClickHandler at the lower index
; actually fired first and consumed every terrain click via deselect-all,
; preventing BPH from ever reaching its confirm-click handler.
;
; L24 fix (2026-05-18, Phase 3 session 5): AttackMoveHandler had the
; SAME inverted-convention bug — sat at idx 0 (fires LAST under reverse-
; tree-order), so its next-click never reached AMH because ClickHandler
; at idx 1 consumed terrain clicks first. Lead live-test confirmed:
; Shift+A → click empty terrain → worker did nothing (camera panned via
; camera_controller polling). Fix: AMH moved to AFTER BuildPlacementHandler
; so its _unhandled_input runs FIRST under reverse-tree-order. Both
; BPH and AMH now correctly conditionally-consume events (placement mode
; for BPH; pending-state for AMH). Companion: attack_move_handler.gd
; now requires `ek.shift_pressed` to enter pending state (plain `A`
; remained a camera-pan-left key per WASD). Camera controller now
; short-circuits horizontal A/D pan when Shift held to prevent
; visible camera drift during attack-move command.
;
; When in placement mode (BPH) or pending mode (AMH) the handler calls
; get_viewport().set_input_as_handled() so the lower-index handlers
; never see the consumed event. When not active, the handler
; short-circuits and lets the other handlers run normally.
[node name="BuildPlacementHandler" type="Node" parent="."]
script = ExtResource("13_buildplacement")

[node name="AttackMoveHandler" type="Node" parent="."]
script = ExtResource("11_attackmove")

